@flexiarg forward-model/flow-toward-controlled-vocabulary
@title Flow The Prose Toward A Controlled Vocabulary
@sigils [⟡/?]
@audience futon stack operators, agents, forward-model authors
@tone conjectural
@style pattern

! conclusion: Make the design patterns themselves computational by flowing their prose slots toward a controlled vocabulary, still English, so each pattern is at once natural language and a formal object.

  + context: Forward-model hypothesis, partially exercised this session. Extends the attested ruling that typed files are the source of truth and prose is regenerated.

  + IF:
    The stack treats typed structure as canonical and derives prose from it, and the design patterns are indexed with their slots individually queryable.

  + HOWEVER:
    The slot contents are still free natural language, so term-flow across patterns, whether one pattern's THEN unifies another's IF, is not yet decidable: the patterns are typed frames with untyped fillers.

  + THEN:
    Census the terms actually used per slot, induce a controlled vocabulary from the corpus, and rewrite the prose slots toward canonical terms while keeping the sentences natural. A controlled vocabulary is the finite term-set over which slot-unification becomes decidable, so the strategy layer becomes a computational object without leaving English.

  + BECAUSE:
    The typed-files ruling made the files typed; this makes the terms typed. It is the same move one level down, and it is what turns the pattern corpus from a description of the strategy into a strategy the machine can compute over.

    + evidence: Bridge target, partially attested this session. Connects to the strategy-as-computational-object note, the per-slot term census, and the iching and iiching controlled-vocabulary precedent.
